sub_title: Master Student in Human Technology Interaction at Eindhoven University of Technology
summary:
I am a result-driven, creative and problem solver person with a background in software and data science. I have graduated from my bachelor in Computer Engineering (CS) which I was in the top 1% of the university entrance exam, and had a merit based scholarship that covers the whole tuition fee, accommodation, and the living expenses during my 5 year education. After graduation, I have started to study Human-Technology Interaction master in Technical University of Eindhoven in September 2022. I have successfully completed the first year, but I am not able to continue the second year because of financial issues. I am currently in search of a full time job.
